The development of the Estonian regilaul (the older folk song), pre-song genres. The compositional principles and poetics of regilaul. Changes of folksongs in connection to cultural thinking. Newer folk songs. Research methods and research history of Estonian folk songObjectives/eesmärkid:  The course provides an overview of the development and changes in Estonian folk songs, their structure, types and research.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. The student is familiar with the main types of Estonian folk songs and related genres; 2. The student has an overview of the structural elements and compositional principles of regilaul; 3. The student is familiar with the diachronic and mental history of the development of Estonian folksong, especially regilaul; 4. The student has an overview of the history of research and publication of Estonian folk songs.
